(177, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-hotnitsa', 'Property in Hotnitsa - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'hotnitsa property for sale, buy properties in hotnitsa', 'Property in Hotnitsa - All the latest properties for sale in Hotnitsa | Veliko Tarnovo', 'Property for sale in Hotnitsa - Veliko Tarnovo municipality of North Bulgaria - The ancient capital of Bulgaria', '<p>The very latest property for sale in Hotnitsa - one of the most sought after villages just 17km from Veliko Tarnovo</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">Hotnitsa is quiet, friendly village of around 500 inhabitants, set in a valley that is surrounded by impressive limestone cliffs. <span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Hotnitsa</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Hotnitsa property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\"><strong>Hotnitsa, Hotnica, Khotnitsa , Hotnitza, Хотница</strong><br /><br /> <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> offers all the basic amenities such as food shops, bars and a post office, how many West European villages today boast three bars and late-opening 7 days a week shops, for a population of around 500 people? There is a regular bus service and good transport links as the Sofia &ndash; Varna highway is just 6km away.  This is why <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> is particularly popular with British buyers looking to buy their new village home in Veliko Tarnovo, Bulgaria.Houses in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> tend to have large plots of land with extremely fertile soil which particularly suits the growth of massive beef tomatoes. So should you decide to look for a house in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong>, look for a house with a large plot for sale in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong>. <br /><br /> <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> is famed for its spectacular waterfall known Kaya Bunar, it forms where the Bohot River leaves the embrace of a limestone Karst canyon and falls 30 metres, forming a small pool with stunningly clear and vivid turquoise colour water. In spring the scent from the flowers is over-powering and one can laze around in the small meadows or have a BBQ next to the waterfall. For the more adventurous there is an Eco-Trail which is marked and is around 2km in distance with (all be it slightly rickety) bridges through a small canyon full of plants, butterflies and small waterfalls.  It&rsquo;s quiet and not at all crowded because only locals know about it, the place has been a popular day trip destination since the Socialist era. Back in those days, there was a restaurant near the waterfall, and the food there used to be so renowned that many people went solely to have a meal, rather than to enjoy the delights of the waterfall. Now the restaurant is overgrown and derelict, perhaps the building is waiting for a new young entrepreneur to come along and re-open it? <br /><br /> Land in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> is also famous for the ancient treasures that plots in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> have relinquished during digs. Some 7,000 years ago, when people had already learnt how to smelt copper into implements and weapons, there was quite a large settlement here. The local inhabitants, however, possessed other valuables, and during these aforementioned excavations archaeologists unearthed under the land in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong>, nearly half a kilo of gold jewelry and coins! These gold rings and plates discovered on a plot in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> are very similar to those of the famous Varna Thracian gold, which is believed to be the oldest forged gold in the world. However, if you choose to buy a house in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> and start digging for gold in your back garden and adjacent plot in <strong>Hotnitsa</strong>, the use of metal detectors in Bulgaria is strictly prohibited with heavy fines if caught! <br /><br /> Historically the village can be acclaimed for &ldquo;those magnificent men in their flying machines&rdquo;, in 1907 the limestone Karst cliffs forming the waterfall were the location for a daring experiment. It was from here that one of Bulgaria\'s first flying machines took off. In effect it was a paraglider and had been designed and built by two local <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> engineers, one of whom was an engineer who was on the design team of the Opera House in Sofia. <br /><br /> Today <strong>Hotnitsa</strong> may be a small, sleepy and quiet village with aspirations towards eco-tourism and being a beautiful place to have a home, but 7000 years ago it was a thriving and busy settlement in one of Europe\'s first civilisations. <br /><br /> Nearest Towns:  Veliko Tarnovo - 15km , Gorna Oryahovitsa - 16km<br /> Nearest Villages:  Resen - 3km, Samovodene - 7km<br /> Post Code: 5058<br /> Area size of village 30.341km2<br /> Altitude 100-195m<br /> Lat 43.15N     Long 25.53333E<br /> <span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Hotnitsa</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Hotnitsa - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-hotnitsa/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(178, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-gorna-lipnitsa', 'Property in Gorna Lipnitsa - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'gorna lipnitsa property for sale, buy properties in gorna lipnitsa', 'Property in Gorna Lipnitsa - All the latest properties for sale in Gorna Lipnitsa | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Gorna Lipnitsa - Pavlikeni municipality of Veliko Tarnovo - The ancient capital of Bulgaria', '<p>The very latest property for sale in Gorna Lipnitsa village - just 37km North of Veliko Tarnovo</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">Gorna Lipnitsa village is located in the central part of The Danube plain, in the small valley of the Jalija brook. The village covers an area of 1500 decares and within these boundaries. Within these boundaries are some substantial sized plots in Gorna Lipnitsa, the surrounding land totals 33 thousand decares and the highest point reaches 160 metres in altitude.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Gorna Lipnitsa property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\"><strong>Gorna Lipnitsa, Gorna Lipnica, Gorna Lipnisa, Gorna Lipnitza, Gornalipnitsa, Горна Липница</strong><br /><br /> The village still has a lot of tree copses and these lend themselves to herding sheep and goats, there is a little vine-growing in the area and most houses in <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong> have vines and variable fruit trees in their large gardens and plots.<br /><br /> Under Turkish occupation people developed a sweet tooth and that motivated them to breed bees which have been passed down by generation in <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong> and now it is very typical to see many different multi coloured bee hives in empty plots in <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong>. After the construction of a monastery school in <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong>, the battle for a church building began. The local Chronicle book tells us about how during the 1850\'s the resistance to build a new church was enormous from both parties &ndash; the Turks and the authorities in Tarnovo. To obtain permission from the sultan, the respected village elders: Hadji Peter Monev, Moni Nikolov, Minch Hadjipetrov and Hadji Lambi Vylchev walked to Tzarigrad and on June 1, 1858 a sultan decree with a date May 24, 1859 was received and in 1863, people in the village succeeded to build the church. It was constructed at the end of the village, next to the Bulgarian graves. The church had not to be domineering because of the Turkish authority\'s opinion and the builders poured the soil from the foundation dig, around the church to make it look small. After the fall of the Ottomans, it was cleaned in front, but to the back, St. Dimitur Church is still the same.<br /><br /> Some architects and professors maintain that the church was built by Koljo Ficheto or some of his scholars influenced by the style of their master and many features including the sculptures of pigeons affirm it most likely. Some of the icons in the church are created by popular icon-painters in Triavna. The new built church was open for visitors and sanctified on the day of its patron &ndash; St. Martyr Dimitrii, on November 8, 1865. At the celebrating ceremony, on the occasion of 100 anniversary of the church birth date, the bishop of Veliko Turnovo declared the church, a cultural monument.<br /><br /> The village had two neighborhoods till the Liberation from Ottoman rule &ndash; a Bulgarian and a Turkish one and they both lived in peace and harmony. There were 36 Turkish and 98 Bulgarian houses in <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong>, up to the Liberation of Turkish rule in 1878. The lime (Lipnitsa) forests, situated to the South of the village gave <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong> its name. Unfortunately, not much is left from those, but at least one lime tree spreads its scent in each of the yards, whilst refreshing tea is made from its blossom. Bulgarian properties in <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong> have big gardens &ndash; quite often 2 decare plots in <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong> per property. Agriculture used to be the main activity in the past and still is, but since it&rsquo;s become so mechanised people try to make a living out of rural tourism. They offer tasty fruits and vegetables from their plots in <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong> during evening gatherings on benches and tables in the streets. A horse and cart, bicycle or a simple walk produces dramatic views around every bend, all these simple Bulgarian lifestyles are being utilised into tourist attractions. At the same time the community centre retains the village&rsquo;s cultural life, as several exhibitions can be seen there: an art one, an ethnographic display, along with an exhibition, dedicated to the Bulgarian writer and journalist Serafim Severniak.  <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong> is the birth place of the famous Bulgarian footballer Trifon Marinov Ivanov who made 77 appearances for Bulgaria scoring 7 goals, including the 1994 World Cup when Bulgaria finished 4th, and being famed for his long range shots and free kicks at goal with many forty five yard shots at goal being witnessed. He was nick named \"the Bulgarian wolf\" after his unshaven looks and long unruly hair with short sides, he started his career playing for Etar Veliko Tarnovo team.<br /><br /> Nearest Towns: Pavlikeni -12km, Polski Trambesh -21km, Veliko Tarnovo -37km<br /> Nearest Villages: Dolna Lipnitsa - 4km, Patresh - 4km, Paskalavets - 9km<br /> Area size of village 37.993km2<br /> Altitude 100 - 199m above sea level<br /> Post code for <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong> - 5227<br /> Latitude: 43.3N Longitude: 25.4E<br /> <span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Gorna Lipnitsa</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Gorna Lipnitsa - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-gorna-lipnitsa/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(179, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-pushevo', 'Property in Pushevo - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Pushevo property for sale, buy properties in Pushevo', 'Property in Pushevo - All the latest properties for sale in Pushevo | Veliko Tarnovo', 'Property for sale in Pushevo - Veliko Tarnovo municipality of North Bulgaria - The ancient capital of Bulgaria', '<p>The very latest property for sale in Pushevo - one of the most sought after villages just 15km from Veliko Tarnovo</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">Pushevo is located on a gently sloping hillside just to the west of Veliko Tarnovo and sat on the banks of the River Yantra and is a quaint and quiet village which comes alive in the evening during summer when everyone meets outside the quaint little village shop which also doubles up as a bar! Many of the Pushevo houses are of a Bulgarian revival style and over 100 years old and there are even houses for sale in Pushevo being this very style!<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Pushevo</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Pushevo property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\"><strong>Pushevo: Pushavo, Пушево</strong><br /><br /> <strong>Pushevo</strong> is first mentioned in demographic and ethnographic study during the 15th century referring to a border dispute between two rural territories of Yuklish <strong>Pushevo</strong> and Balvan <strong>Pushevo</strong> in the area of \"Iklesh.\" This study confirms that the village <strong>Pushevo</strong> existed in its current location dur