trong>Belyakovets</strong> lies within a limestone Karst area having a number of caves, a lake (Lake <strong>Belyakovets</strong>), fresh water springs and an abundance of flora and fauna. It has been inhabited since Neolithic times and Neolithic remains and artifacts have been found in the nearby caves. There are some beautiful walks such as to the Preobrazhenski Monastery and along the brook whose source is the <strong>Belyakovets</strong> lake and where it finishes in Samovodene, from where you can catch a bus back to Veliko Tarnovo and then back to <strong>Belyakovets</strong>, a lovely Sunday walk! <br /><br /> <strong>Belyakovets</strong> has very good infrastructure and provides everything for your everyday needs including shops, bars, a library and community centre. There is very regular public transport into Veliko Tarnovo with a good road providing access throughout the year. The major schools in Veliko Tarnovo are therefore serviced regularly including the English American School. Therefore if a family is looking to purchase a large family home then a house in <strong>Belyakovets</strong> will certainly tick all the boxes! <br /><br /> Please find below, a full list of the latest Property for sale in <strong>Belyakovets</strong><br /><br /> Nearest Town: Veliko Tarnovo 5km<br /> Nearest Village:  Ledenik 3km<br /> Altitude: 300 - 499m above sea level<br /> Area size of Village of <strong>Belyakovets</strong>: 22.497km2<br /> Post code: 5031<br /> Latitude: 43.1N Longitude: 25.58333E<br /> <span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Belyakovets</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Belyakovets - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-pr