(183, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-arbanasi', 'Property in Arbanasi - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Arbanasi property for sale, buy properties in Arbanasi', 'Property in Arbanasi - All the latest properties for sale in Arbanasi | Veliko Tarnovo', 'Property for sale in Arbanasi - One of the most visited tourist destinations in Bulgaria', '<p>The very latest property for sale in Arbanasi - The Arbanasi Architectural Reserve is one of the most popular tourist destinations in Bulgaria</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village of Arbanasi is one of the most important tourist destinations in Bulgaria. Just 5km from Veliko Tarnovo, Arbanasi with its traditional architecture, museums and churches is one of the most beatiful villages in all Bulgaria.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Arbanasi</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Arbanasi property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\"><strong>Arbanasi, Arbanassi, Arbanaci, Арбанаси</strong><br /><br /> <strong>Arbanasi</strong> has derived its name from the Albanian word Arbanas, which means \"worker of the land\". The Turkish used the term \"arnavut\" for Albanians and Macedonians of whom many settled in this part of Bulgaria after Bulgarian boyars came from the westernmost regions of the Second Bulgarian Empire in the 13th century. Now it&rsquo;s famed as the <strong>Arbanasi</strong> Architectural Reserve, with the houses in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> being mainly of the revival style and new houses and properties in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> being strictly regulated and particularly the hotels in <strong>Arbanasi</strong>, since they clearly have an impact on spatial planning and scale of the architectural reserve. The village of <strong>Arbanasi</strong> is located on a high plateau at an average height above sea level of 400 metres.<br /><br /> Suleiman the Magnificent, Ottoman Sultan, mentioned <strong>Arbanasi</strong> in 1538 by writing that the villages main activities were animal husbandry and commercial trading some of this trading included silk thread and local residents bred silkworms. Nowadays you won&rsquo;t find silkworms or thread for sale but many traditional garments, antiques and local art and craft wares share the pavements with <strong>Arbanasi</strong> hotel frontages. <br /><br /> During the 17th century, <strong>Arbanasi</strong> became renowned as a centre of trade and commerce. Merchants from <strong>Arbanasi</strong> were prominent and sold and exchanged wares throughout the Turkish Empire. The houses in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> of these well to do merchants were in effect manor houses verging on small castles appearing menacing from the outside with no balconies or terraces, as is the architectural signature of revival style <strong>Arbanasi</strong> houses, they had bars on the windows and impenetrable armoured entrance ways. However, once inside they were lavish and impressed their owners guests decorated with exceptionally ornate woodcarvings and detailed joinery with plastered mouldings adorning walls of these houses in <strong>Arbanasi</strong>. Another characteristic of the houses in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> was due to their design and construction the occupants could remain inside for long periods of time only venturing out into the inner courtyard to collect water from the well. <br /><br /> In the early 18th century <strong>Arbanasi</strong> was looted and raised to the ground by fire at the hands of mercenaries hired by the Ottoman Empire after this and an epidemic of cholera, residents were forced to move on and <strong>Arbanasi</strong> went through its darkest period with houses losing their timber roofs and interiors and thus just becoming plots in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> waiting for redevelopment. <br /><br /> After the early 19th century <strong>Arbanasi</strong> gradually started to resemble what can be seen today. New settlers arrived from the Greek and Tryavna Balkan regions bringing local vernacular skill sets being mingled with the dominant Tarnovo revival, which turned desolate plots in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> into revival period architectural masterpieces which can still be seen in this architectural reserve, such as the Konstantzalieva house amongst 80 or so unique houses in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> others are the Hadji-ilieva, Hadji-kostova, Chamurova, Kandilarova and Lecheva houses in <strong>Arbanasi</strong>. <br /><br /> Places of interest include a visit to the Konstantsaliev House, The Birth of Christ Church, and The Church of the Archangels Michael and Gabriel. The Birth of Christ Church is amongst the oldest of properties in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> and the narthex has murals dating from 1597 including murals of \"The Last Judgment\" and \"The Birth of Christ\". Also The Holy Archangels Michael and Gabriel Church is an architectural and cultural monument of Bulgaria declared so in a state gazette in 1978, murals in this church include \"The Descent into Hell\" and a different rendition of \"The Birth of Christ\". Saint Dimiter Church is another architectural and cultural monument located in the centre and surrounded by houses in <strong>Arbanasi</strong>, it can be difficult to spot immediately. The church dates back to the 16th century giving it the title of being the oldest surviving property in <strong>Arbanasi</strong>, being completed in 1621. The Saint George Church and is a massive stone structure being 21 x 12 metres dating back from the end of the 17th century and archeological digs have revealed that an earlier cathedral once existed here dating from the 16th century. The Saint Atanas Church was built during the 1630s and the icons in this church were completed in 1667. The <strong>Arbanasi</strong> Monastery - St. Virgin Mary is located on the outskirts of the village, off the road to Gorna Oryahovitsa. The convent contains the miraculous icon of the Weeping Virgin, or 3 armed virgin! According to legend after destruction of Tsarevets by the Ottomans in 1396 the nuns left the convent and buried the icons in the grounds, years later a shepherd heard weeping from a plot in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> and discovered the icon returning it to the monastery.  There is a yearly festival on August 15 (the Day of the Virgin) and pilgrims travel and visit this place of worship. In The Saint Nikola Church another icon of the Virgin Mary can be found and this icon by legend rewards women with powers of fertility after praying before the icon and leaving an offering of a stotinka coin, should the coin stick then the virgin has heard their prayers, should the coin fall to the ground.....pray harder next time! <br /><br /> <strong>Arbanasi</strong> has some beautiful restaurants offering traditional delicious home cooked fare in the stone walled gardens which define the plots in <strong>Arbanasi</strong>. There are many quality hotels in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> many with swimming pools and beautiful architectural styling from the revival period since being converted from a house or built as a purpose designed guest house in <strong>Arbanasi</strong>. At the other end of the scale are large <strong>Arbanasi</strong> hotels offering banqueting facilities and are especially popular in Summer for wedding functions with couples coming from as far as Sofia and mixing their wedding in the hotel in <strong>Arbanasi</strong> with a visit to <strong>Arbanasi</strong> Monastery - St. Virgin Mary to hopefully ensure that they will have a happy future family! <br /><br /> Please find below, a full list of the latest Property for sale in <strong>Arbanasi</strong><br /><br /> Nearest Town:   Veliko Tarnovo 4km, Gorna Oryahovitsa 4km, Lyaskovets 5km<br /> Nearest Village:  Sheremetya  4km, Malki Chiflik 6km, Parvomaytsi 8km, Dragizhevo <br />8km Altitude: 300 - 499m above sea level<br /> Area size of Village of <strong>Arbanasi</strong>: 11.881km2<br /> Post code: 5029<br /> Latitude: 43.1N Longitude: 25.667E<br /> <span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Arbanasi</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Arbanasi - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-arbanasi/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(184, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-balvan', 'Property in Balvan - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Belyakovets property for sale, buy properties in Belyakovets', 'Property in Balvan - All the latest properties for sale in Balvan | Veliko Tarnovo', 'Property for sale in Balvan - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality of North Bulgaria', '<p>The very latest property for sale in Balvan - A popular village just 20km North West of Veliko Tarnovo</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">Balvan is surrounded by quiet countryside with two rivers close by and several lakes offering opportunities for rural tourism and fishing.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Balvan</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Balvan property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\"><strong>Balvan, Bulvan, Bolvan, Балван</strong><br /><br /> <strong>Balvan</strong> is a small well developed village just off the E772 main Sofia &ndash; Varna highway, allowing you to get to Veliko Tarnovo within about 10 minutes, surrounded by rolling hills the village is primarily an agricultural centre, although it has shown some recent development regarding grain storage with being so close to the E772. <br /><br /> The houses in <strong>Balvan</strong> have particularly large gardens with outbuildings and stone barns being associated with plots in <strong>Balvan</strong>.<br /><br /> <strong>Balvan</strong> has a large central square and a shop and busy little bar with frequent buses to Sevlievo and Veliko Tarnovo from the bus stop situated near the shop and bar. <br /><br /> Close by is the Emen gorge with its ecotrail which wanders down the gorge providing breathtaking scenery. <br /><br /> Please find below, a full list of the latest Property for sale in <strong>Balvan</strong><br /><br /> Nearest Towns:  Veliko Tarnovo &ndash; 20km<br /> Nearest Villages:  Novo Selo &ndash; 2km, Vetrintsi &ndash; 3.9km<br /> Area size of Village of <strong>Balvan</strong>: 33.67km2 <br /> Altitude: 300 - 499m above sea level<br /> Post code: 5064<br /> Latitude: 43.083N Longitude: 25.417E<br /> <span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Balvan</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Balvan - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-balvan/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(185, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-novo-selo', 'Property in Novo Selo - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Novo Selo property for sale, buy properties in Novo Selo', 'Property in Novo Selo - All the latest properties for sale in Novo selo | Veliko Tarnovo', 'Property for sale in Novo Selo - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality of North Bulgaria', '<p>The very latest property for sale in Novo Selo &ndash; The first village of Veliko Tarnovo municipality.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">Novo Selo is a highly sought after village at the western limit of the Veliko Tarnovo Region; it lies just off the main Sofia-Varna road and is very conveniently located for travel to Sofia which can be reached in just over 2 hours.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Novo Selo</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Novo Selo property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\"><strong>Novo Selo, Novo Celo, Novo Sello, Novo Cello, Ново село</strong><br /><br /> This is one of the most desirable villages to acquire a house in Veliko Tarnovo region due to its close proximity and easy access to town.  <strong>Novo Selo</strong> has all the local facilities needed to enjoy everyday living such as shops, three bars, medical centre, dentist, a primary school and a regular bus service into town. The houses in <strong>Novo Selo</strong> tend to have large plots averaging over 1000m2 and growing your own produce in the garden of your property in <strong>Novo Selo</strong> is a popular pastime. <br /><br /> <strong>Novo Selo</strong> is the birthplace of Matey \"Mitkaloto\" Preobrazhenski who took an active part in the revolution against the Ottoman Empire and accompanied Vasil Levski  on his tour of Bulgaria to establish revolutionary committees. He was always travelling around the country and this is why he was given the nickname \"Mitkaloto\" meaning \"The Wandering One\".  He was an orphan and attended the Dryanovo Monastery to serve as a monk. Later, he moved to the Preobrazhenski (Transfiguration) Monastery between Veliko Tarnovo and Samovodene.In 1850 he produced the \"circle of nature and life\" in a calendar known as \"The Perpetual Calendar\" which measures time and can now be seen in the History Museum in Pavlikeni. The calendar illustrates that human life follows the same circle as the four seasons in nature. He died in <strong>Novo Selo</strong> in March 1875 and the statue and tomb of Matei Preobrazhenski can be seen on your right hand side as you travel to Veliko Tarnovo just after <strong>Novo Selo</strong> and is a popular stopping point. <br /><br /> The highest peak in Veliko Tarnovo municipality is located in the village of <strong>Novo Selo</strong> and there is a triangulation sign placed accordingly at 560 metres above sea level. Towards the south of the village, were found fossils of brachiopods, belemnites, shellfish, corals, and snails dating back 130 million years and only 2km  northwest of <strong>Novo Selo</strong> a Thracian burial mound was discovered in 1975 and it was excavated to discover that the base is surrounded with a wall of rough stones and in it was buried a fully armed Thracian commander with his horse who were in effect cremated simultaneously by burning on the floor. A clay bowl and a small clay pot and a badly burnt iron sword and iron axe were also discovered. All these artifacts found in <strong>Novo Selo</strong> are on exhibition in the Historical Museum of Veliko Tarnovo. <br /><br /> Please find below, a full list of the latest property for sale in <strong>Novo Selo</strong>. <br /><br /> Nearest towns &ndash; Veliko Tarnovo 22km, Sevlievo 24km<br /> Nearest villages - Balvan 5km, Vetrintsi 8km<br /> Area size of village 41.868km2 Altitude 300 - 499m<br /> Post code: 5069<br /> Latitude: 43.067N Longitude: 25.367E<br /> <span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Novo Selo</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Novo Selo - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-novo-selo/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(186, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-debelets', 'Property in Novo Selo - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Debelets property for sale, buy properties in Debelets', 'Property in Debelets - All the latest properties for sale in Debelets | Veliko Tarnovo', 'Property for sale in Debelets - Veliko Tarnovo Municipality of North Bulgaria', '<p>The town of Debelets is situated on the South East side of the Belichinata valley near to the Belitsa river.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">Debelets is a small, well maintained town with good roads and an excellent range of facilities including a post office, vet, pharmacy, supermarket, bars, cafes and restaurants. In the centre, near the town hall there is a nice park and children&rsquo;s play area with fountains and flowers, adjacent are apartments in Debelets.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Debelets</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Debelets property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\"><strong>Debelets, Debeletz, Debelez, Debelec, Дебелец</strong><br /><br /> <strong>Debelets</strong> has regular bus services to Veliko Tarnovo and the surrounding villages.  The town is surrounded by pine forests which are interspersed with large houses in <strong>Debelets</strong> which overlook the Stara Planina mountain range in the distant and unspoiled countryside. Also with the Belitsa river running through the centre there is ample opportunity to go fishing and plots for sale in <strong>Debelets</strong> on the banks of the river are rare investment opportunities. <br /><br /> The traditional town fair of <strong>Debelets</strong> is celebrated on the first Sunday of August where you can enjoy a concert during the evening before in the town square. <br /><br /> There is a 300 year old bridge on the Belitsa river in <strong>Debelets</strong> and two churches in the town are also worth a visit - \"Saint Marina\" and \"Saint Mary Source\".  The second one was built by Stefan Rabatilya who was a student of Kolyo Ficheto. <br /><br /> Please find below, a full list of the latest Property for sale in <strong>Debelets</strong><br /><br /> Nearest towns:  Veliko Tarnovo &ndash; 5km, Kilifarevo &ndash; 5km<br /> Nearest village: Prisovo &ndash; 3km<br /> Area size of <strong>Debelets</strong>: 26.375km2<br /> Altitude: 100 - 199m above sea level<br /> Post code: 5030<br /> Latitude: 43.03333N Longitude: 25.61667E<br /> <span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Debelets</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Debelets - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-debelets/page-1', 'Desktop');
