aint George. The only monument in commemoration of the soldiers fallen for the freedom of Bulgaria to be found in Gorna Oryahovitsa region is placed in the yard of the church. Yantra River offers great conditions for fishing, family day outs and picnics and sunbathing.<br/><br/>\r\nNearest Town:  Dolna Oryahovitsa – 8 km, Lyaskovets – 14 km, Gorna Oryahovitsa – 16 km, Strazhitsa – 16 km, Veliko Tarnovo – 27 km<br/>\r\nNearest Villages:  Pisarevo – 4 km, Gorski Dolen Trambesh – 5 km, Dzhulyunitsa – 9 km<br/>\r\nAltitude: 56 m above sea level<br/>\r\nArea size of the village: 22 km2<br/>\r\nPost code: 5128<br/>\r\nLatitude: 43.181 N Longitude: 25.823 Е<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Varbitsa</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Varbitsa - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-varbitsa/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(317, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-paisiy', 'Property in Paisiy - Gorna Oryahovitsa Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'paisiy property for sale, buy properties in paisiy', 'Property in Paisiy - All the latest properties for sale in Paisiy', 'Property for sale in Paisiy - Gorna Oryahovitsa municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>The very latest property for sale in Paisiy - a small and peaceful village which enchants with its timelessness</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village is a heavenly place where you can have a full relaxation and recharge your energy.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Paisiy<strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Paisiy property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\"><strong>Paisiy</strong> is a small, serene village, located 40 min north-west from Veliko Tarnovo. The village has a town hall. It received its present days name in 1934. Before that it was called Arnauti. Due to its altitude and the abundance of old growth forests the climate is very mild with fresh and cool air. The population of the village is around 200 people.<br/><br/>\r\nAncient artefacts dating back from roman times and the neolithic period were found near <strong>Paisiy</strong>. There are also the remains of an important Roman road which passed near the village ages ago. <strong>Paisiy</strong> lies in the bottom of a dale. The areas surrounding it are really beautiful and they are much preferred places for recreation. Close to the village you will find 3 dams; they attract many fishermen