(344, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-byala-cherkva', 'Property in Byala Cherkva - Pavlikeni Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Byala Cherkva property for sale, buy properties in Byala Cherkva', 'Property in Byala Cherkva - All the latest properties for sale in Byala Cherkva | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Byala Cherkva - Pavlikeni municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Byala Cherkva is a small but well-developed town providing a peaceful way of life</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The town has a rich ancient history and is a great place for a new home in a serene setting<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Byala Cherkva</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Byala Cherkva property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Byala Cherkva is just 5 km away from Pavlikeni and 35 km north-west of Veliko Tarnovo. It is a small but well-developed town with good infrastructure. It has general stores, a school, kindergarten, community centre, pharmacy, 3 doctor’s offices, 5 museums, a town park and regular public transport to neighbouring towns and villages. Biala Cherkva was declared a town in 1976. Its population is around 3000 people.<br/><br/>\r\n<strong>Byala Cherkva</strong> has very rich ancient history; a Roman road used to pass through it and the town also took active participation in the struggle for Bulgarian freedom from Ottoman rule. The main way of earning one’s living used to be agriculture and viticulture. The area is well-developed and attracts many people looking for a new home. The beautiful natire, fresh air and peaceful setting also drive many tourist here. Rositsa River runs through the village thus rendering he vicinity great for hunting and fishing and even for sun bathing.<br/><br/>\r\nNearest Town: Pavlikeni – 5 km, Veliko Tarnovo – 37 km, Polski Trambesh – 38 km<br/>\r\nNearest Villages:  Vishovgrad – 7 km, Mihaltsi – 8 km, Stambolovo – 9 km<br/>\r\nAltitude: 104 m above sea level<br/>\r\nArea size of the village: 38 km2<br/>\r\nPost code: 5220<br/>\r\nLatitude: 43.200 N Longitude: 25.299 E<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Byala Cherkva</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Byala Cherkva - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-byala-cherkva/page-1', 'Desktop');
