(345, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-daskot', 'Property in Daskot - Pavlikeni Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Daskot property for sale, buy properties in Daskot', 'Property in Daskot - All the latest properties for sale in Daskot | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Daskot - Pavlikeni municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Daskot is a small and peaceful village that will enchant you with its beauty</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village is the excellent place for a new home away from the hustle and bustle of big cities<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Daskot</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Daskot property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Daskot is located 8 km away from Pavlikeni and 31 km north-west of Veliko Tarnovo. The village is small but well-developed and with good infrastructure; it has general stores, a cafe, a doctor’s office, kindergarten, community centre, post office, internet, good mobile network and regular public transport no neighbouring towns and villages. There are around 10 british ex-pat families living in the village. The population is roughly 500; people are friendly and hospitable.<br/><br/>\r\nThe village hosts the folklore fest The Humour in Folk Art annually. Villagers make their living predominantly by farming and cattle breeding. One of the largest egg producing factories in Bulgaria is based in <strong>Daskot</strong> and you will also find a nursery garden there. An interesting fact is that the communist head of state from recent past Todor Zhivkov met his life MD Mara Maleeva in this very village. There are a few dams close to the settlement and a river runs close by; the area is very beautiful and a great place for hunting, fishing and relaxation.<br/><br/>\r\nNearest Town: Pavlikeni – 5 km, Byala cherkva – 12 km, Veliko Tarnovo – 35 km, Polski Trambesh – 36 km<br/>\r\nNearest Villages:  Lesicheri – 5 km, Paskalevets – 8 km, Dichin – 10 km, Stambolovo – 13 km<br/>\r\nAltitude: 200 – 299 m above sea level<br/>\r\nArea size of the village: 31.472 km2<br/>\r\nPost code: 5223<br/>\r\nLatitude: 43.250 N Longitude: 25.399 E<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Daskot</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Daskot - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-daskot/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(346, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-dimcha', 'Property in Dimcha- Pavlikeni Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Dimcha property for sale, buy properties in Dimcha', 'Property in Dimcha - All the latest properties for sale in Dimcha | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Dimcha - Pavlikeni municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Dimcha is a well-developed village offering many ways for recreation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village is located in a region famous for its authentic countryside spirit.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Dimcha</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Dimcha property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Dimcha is situated 46 km north-west of Veliko Tarnovo. The settlement has general stores, town hall, church, community centre, library and a kindergarten. The village is small and locals are very harmonious; they regularly organize various events and parties. There is also the contest for the tastiest home made marmalade. <strong>Dimcha</strong> has regular public transport to neighbouring towns and villages. Its population is roughly 400 people.<br/><br/>\r\n20 min away from Dimcha is the Alexander Stamboliyski dam which provides great conditions and facilities for various water sports, fishing and recreation. There are a few caves that could be visited, as well as a number of beautiful natural sites. The area provides great opportunities for outings, hiking, fishing and relaxation. The village is small, but close to a town with all necessary amenities. The region is known for its wines and traditional Bulgarian rural atmosphere.<br/><br/>\r\nNearest Town: Suhindol – 10 km, Pavlikeni – 10 km, Polski Trambesh – 43 km, Veliko Tarnovo – 46 km<br/>\r\nNearest Villages:  Varbovka – 3 km, Krasno Gradishte – 6 km, Butovo – 12 km<br/>\r\nAltitude: 231 m above sea level<br/>\r\nArea size of the village: 20,573 km2<br/>\r\nPost code: 5234<br/>\r\nLatitude: 43.216 N Longitude: 25.200 E<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Dimcha</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Dimcha - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-dimcha/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(347, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-dolna-lipnitsa', 'Property in Dolna Lipnitsa - Pavlikeni Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Dolna Lipnitsa property for sale, buy properties in Dolna Lipnitsa', 'Property in Dolna Lipnitsa - All the latest properties for sale in Dolna Lipnitsa | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Dolna Lipnitsa - Pavlikeni municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Dolna Lipnitsa is big and well developed village with a rich history dating back to the Middle Ages</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">It is surrounded by pure nature, fresh air and peaceful atmosphere.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Dolna Lipnitsa</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Dolna Lipnitsa property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Dolna Lipnitsa has a well developed infrastructure, about 16 km. southwest of the town of Polski Trumbesh known for its healing mineral springs and 40km. northwest from Veliko Tarnovo. Near the village is the lake suitable for fishing and beach in the summer, but also in the region have the opportunity to hunt various game species.<br/><br/>\r\nThe village has several food shops, cafes, restaurants, gas station, medical centre with doctor and dentist, kindergarten, school and regular transport to nearby towns and villages. One of the most beautiful and ancient churches in Northern Bulgaria is located in <strong>Dolna Lipnitsa</strong> . Town hall, post office and bus station located in the village centre. The village has a choir for folk music and folk dances. Dolna Lipnitsa is known for its local dishes - Lipnishka salad, nettle stew, Dogalach - kind of pulled pie, vinegar sop, Prazenitsa, Greaves and onion.<br/><br/>\r\nFounded in VII-XII century AD, <strong>Dolna Lipnitsa</strong> became one of the centres of enlightened movement in Northern Bulgaria during the Renaissance. The main attraction in the beautiful centre of the village is the monument to those who died for freedom and unification of Bulgaria warriors and cannon from First World War.<br/><br/>\r\nNear the village is situated the \"Lily Mound\", which was inhabited by the ancient Thracians and during the First World War was used for military purposes.<br/><br/>\r\nThe nearest cities: Polish Trambesh -16 km, Pavlikem - 18 km <br/>\r\nThe nearest villages: Obedinenie - 4 km, Gorna Lipnitsa - 5 km, Ivancha - 10 km, Patresh - 10 km<br/>\r\nArea size of Village of Dolna Lipnitsa: 42,945 km2<br/>\r\nPostal Code: 5199<br/>\r\nAltitude 156 m<br/>\r\nCoordinates: 43.317 ° N, 25.467 ° E.<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Dolna Lipnitsa</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Dolna Lipnitsa- Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-dolna-lipnitsa/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(348, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-karaisen', 'Property in Karaisen - Pavlikeni Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Karaisen property for sale, buy properties in Karaisen', 'Property in Karaisen - All the latest properties for sale in Karaisen | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Karaisen - Pavlikeni municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Karaisen is a large village offering necessary amenities and close to the main road</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village is lively and is a great place for a new home abroad away from the hustle and bustle of big towns.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Karaisen</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Karaisen property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Karaisen is situated in the Danube plain and is the largest village in Pavlikeni Municipality. The village is well-developed and has a green market, pharmacy, town hall, community centre, library, kindergarten, elementary school as well as general stores and pubs. The settlement is probably named after a man called Kara Asen who helped the village during an epidemic outbreak. The population of <strong>Karaisen</strong> is around 1100 people.<br/><br/>\r\nKaraisen has a winery as well a small UPVC windows factory. A Market Day is held every Monday and the year is full of events and rituals and customs enactments. One of them is Ivanovi Vlachugi when the most recently wed couple in the village is ‘dragged’ to a water fountain to be ‘washed’; this is done for health and prosperity and happens annually on 7th January. The area offers great conditions for fishing and hunting – Studena River runs through the village and close to the village is <strong>Karaisen</strong> Dam. There are good transport links to neighbouring villages and town and the main arterial road Sofia – Ruse is 7 km away from Karaisen.<br/><br/>\r\nNearest Town: Pavlikeni – 16 km, Polski Trambesh – 33 km, Veliko Tarnovo – 56 km<br/>\r\nNearest Villages: Batak – 3 km, Slomer – 6 km, Gorna Studena – 12 km<br/>\r\nAltitude: 73 m above sea level<br/>\r\nArea size of the village: 49,536 km2<br/>\r\nPost code: 5230<br/>\r\nLatitude: 43.382 N Longitude: 25.350 E<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Karaisen</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Karaisen - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-karaisen/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(349, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-lesicheri', 'Property in Lesicheri - Pavlikeni Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Lesicheri property for sale, buy properties in Lesicheri', 'Property in Lesicheri - All the latest properties for sale in Lesicheri | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Lesicheri - Pavlikeni municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Lesicheri is a picturesque and serene village that arose somewhere around the 15 - 16 century</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village is well-developed and offers great opportunities for recreation and relaxation.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Lesicheri</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Lesicheri property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Lesicheri is located 5 km away from Pavlikeni and 31 km north-west of Veliko Tarnovo. The village is well-developed and with good infrastructure. It has a beautiful church built in 1873 by apprentices of the renowned Bulgarian master builder Kolyo Ficheto; it bears the architecture characteristic of that time. The settlement has good mobile coverage and digital TV; also offers general stores, pubs, school, kindergarten, village hall, community centre, doctor’s office and a railway station. There is also regular public transport to neighbourhood town and villages. There are two theories regarding the origin of the name of the village. One of them states that it is derived from the word les (which means forest) and the other claims that the first settler was called Lesko. The population of the village is around 500 people.<br/><br/>\r\n<strong>Lesicheri</strong> was founded in 15-16 century. There are numerous archaeological items found in the vicinity; there are also traces of an ancient settlement near Lesicheri. The Lesicheri pillar, known also as the Marko’s Obelisk, is an 11 m high gravestone located in the vicinity; it is dated back to the 2nd – 4th century. Market gardening is widely practised in the area. Close to the village you will find 2 dams and Rositsa River runs 1 km away making the region great for fishing, hunting, hiking and picnicking. The vicinity is peaceful and beautiful is a great place for a nice day out among the nature.<br/><br/>\r\nNearest Town: Pavlikeni – 13 km, Veliko Tarnovo – 30 km, Polski Trambesh – 32 km<br/>\r\nNearest Villages: Daskot – 5 km, Dichin – 5 km, Stambolovo – 9 km<br/>\r\nAltitude: 82 m above sea level<br/>\r\nArea size of the village: 25,796 km2<br/>\r\nPost code: 5222<br/>\r\nLatitude: 43.216 N Longitude: 25.433 E<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Lesicheri</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Lesicheri - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-lesicheri/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(350, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-musina', 'Property in Musina - Pavlikeni Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Karaisen property for sale, buy properties in Musina', 'Property in Musina - All the latest properties for sale in Musina | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Musina - Pavlikeni municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Village of Musina is known for its many natural attractions and is a very popular tourist destination. </p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village is located near the highway E-772 (Sofia-Varna), making it convenient and yet quiet location.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Musina</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Musina property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Near the village of Musina is a cave and karst spring located next to it. The spring  is called \"Musinski spring\" and forms the River Cave, which is strait of Negovanka river. In ancient times, the waters of the spring were evacuated by special plumbing to the ancient town of Nicopolis ad Istrum near the village Nikyup.<br/><br/>\r\nTraces from primitive era were found in the Musinska cave. The roots of the village date back to ancient times and are related to the ancient Roman town of Nicopolis ad Istrum, which was founded by the Emperor Trajan in 106 AD. As <strong>Musina</strong> the village is known shortly after the fall of Bulgaria under Ottoman rule when the village was based and its name comes from the famous Musyo leader.<br/><br/>\r\nNear the village is the local landmark \"gap\", called by locals - \"hole\". This landmark is located just 400 meters south of Musina and represents two adjacent and connected by underground karst chasms gallery. If you dare, you can lower the 27-meter pits specially built spiral staircase. You can go down to the bottom by stairs and next to them has a gazebo for relaxation and enjoying the beautiful view of the surroundings. Cave and pitfalls associated with Emenska underground cave, which is part of Emen kanyon. These two pits are not the only part of the beauty that you can witness in this pristine and rich area.<br/><br/>\r\nIn 1790 was opened first school in the region. In 1938 was completed new church \"Sv. Paraskeva \", which was renovated in 2009. Tourists and residents of the village of <strong>Musina</strong> can enjoy the attractions offered by the small holiday complex in the village, such as fishing, archery, badminton and cycling. The complex has an outdoor pool, barbecue, bar, parking and more.<br/><br/>\r\nThe nearest cities: Pavlikem -14.6 km, Veliko Tarnovo - 23.5 km<br/>\r\nThe nearest villages: Rusalya - 3 km, Mihaltsi - 7 km<br/>\r\nArea size of Village of Musina: 23,349 km2<br/>\r\nPostal Code: 5247<br/>\r\nAltitude 233 m<br/>\r\nCoordinates: 43.15 ° N, 25.433 ° E<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Musina</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Musina - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-musina/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(351, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-nedan', 'Property in Nedan - Pavlikeni Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Nedan property for sale, buy properties in Nedan', 'Property in Nedan - All the latest properties for sale in Nedan | Pavlikeni', 'Property for sale in Nedan - Pavlikeni municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Nedan is large and lively village with all the necessary amenities where you can live a peaceful life</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village will enchant you with its lovely atmosphere and friendly and hospitable people you will meet there.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Nedan</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Nedan property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">The village of Nedan is well-developed and offers all the necessary amenities you might need. It is located in the Danube plain, 9 km north-west of Pavlikeni. There is regular transport to the neighbouring villages and towns. The settlement has a village hall, elementary school, kindergarten pensioners club, grocery stores and pubs. <strong>Nedan</strong> also has its own football club. Its population is roughly 1400.<br/><br/>\r\nThere is a poultry farm in the village. An interesting fact is that there is an extinct volcano in the Chatala area, close to the neighbouring village of Butovo. It was active 2 million years ago. The vicinity of Nedan offers beautiful nature, peace and tranquility and fresh air – excellent conditions for eco-tourism, walks, picnics and family day outs among the nature. This i