(378, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-ruhovtsi', 'Property in Ruhovtsi - Elena Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Ruhovtsi property for sale, buy properties in Ruhovtsi', 'Property in Ruhovtsi- All the latest properties for sale in Ruhovtsi | Elena', 'Property for sale in Ruhovtsi - Elena municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>Ruhovtsi is a picturesque mountain village, which is situated among the gorgeous scenery of the mountain</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">This small mountain village is situated near the town of Elena, only 7 km.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Ruhovtsi</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Ruhovtsi property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Ruhovtsi is located in the heart of the Elena Balkan paradise attracts many tourists in the area. The village is only 10 min. from Elena and 44 km. Veliko Tarnovo. In the village there is a community centre established on the January 19 1914 and churches built in 1859, and near the village were found remains of an old monastery.<br/><br/>\r\n<strong>Ruhovtsi</strong> village exists as a village since before the liberation. The village has been recorded Turkish sources occurs as Ruholare. One hypothesis for the name of the village comes from the name of the first settler Ruho old man from Elena, who was looking for places for his herd. The second hypothesis is that it is based at the end of the XVI century by the old man Ruho, who was one of the settlers from Radomir village Rusolare. The settlement was officially announced as village after 1887.<br/><br/> \r\nFrom the village there are marked tourist routes to the natural landmark Hristovskiyat falls of Borushtitsa River. On the river there are rest areas with tables, benches, barbecue and outbreaks. In the river that runs through Ruhovtsi and in the nearby lake, you can fish or cool during the hot summer days.<br/><br/> \r\nThe area is very suitable for rural and eco tourism and hunting tourism, as in the nearby woods there are many and varied game such as deer, boar, pheasant and wild goats.<br/><br/>\r\nBuying property here, you will be able to enjoy the beauty of this heavenly place. The virgin nature and the coolness of the Elena Balkan will make you forget the hectic pace of the big city and relax fully.<br/><br/>\r\nThe nearest cities: Elena - 7 km, Zlatarica - 21 km, Veliko Tarnovo - 44 km<br/>\r\nThe nearest villages: Hristovtsi - 2 km, Ilakov rat - 3 km, Maryan - 4.6 km<br/>\r\nArea size of village of Ruhovtsi: 9,638 km2<br/>\r\nPostal Code: 5079<br/>\r\nAltitude: 367 m<br/>\r\nCoordinates: 42.916 ° N, 25.950 ° E<br/>\r\n<span id=\"link_hide\" class=\"clear_l pointer mt_5px f_right display_none\" style=\"display: none;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_view\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Hide information about <strong>Ruhovtsi</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_up.png\" alt=\"Ruhovtsi - Hide\" /> </span></div>', 'www.yantrahomes.co.uk/en/fast-search-results/latest-property-ruhovtsi/page-1', 'Desktop'),
(379, 'en', 'fast-search-results', 'latest-property-maryan', 'Property in Maryan - Elena Municipality Bulgaria | Yantra Homes', 'Maryan property for sale, buy properties in Maryan', 'Property in Maryan- All the latest properties for sale in Maryan | Elena', 'Property for sale in Maryan - Elena municipality in the Veliko Tarnovo Region of North Bulgaria', '<p>The village of Maryan is a piece of heaven which offers unique nature, fresh mountain air and perfect serenity</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0;\">The village is set in the heart of Elena Balkan, just 8 km away from Elena and 46 km away from Veliko Tarnovo and is one of the oldest villages in Elena region.<span id=\"link_view\" class=\"clear_l pointer f_right mt_5px\" style=\"display: block;\" onclick=\"$(\'div#text_more\').slideToggle(); $(this).hide(); $(\'span#link_hide\').show();\"> <span class=\"link\">Read more about <strong>Maryan</strong></span> <img style=\"display: inline; float: none; width: 8px;\" src=\"application/images/arrow_down.png\" alt=\"Maryan property &ndash; Read More\" /> </span></h3>\r\n<div id=\"text_more\" class=\"clear_l mt_10px display_none fs_13px a_justify \" style=\"width: 672px; color: #4a4a4a; display: none;\">Maryan has ancient history. Remains of a basilica which were dated back to the V or VI c. were found in the northern end of the settlement. Also marble pillars and capitals from the same period were uncovered there. The name of Maryan is probably derived from the name of Tsar Ivan Alexander’s daughter Kera Tamara, also known as Mara or the Fair Mara. She was also the sister of Tsar Ivan Shishman – the last ruler of the Second Bulgarian Kingdom. The village hosts a small winery which produces wine in limited boutique series. There is also a church and a community centre. The population of Maryan is roughly 100 people.<br/><br/>\r\nThe village of <strong>Maryan</strong> is set in a spectacular natural setting. The surrounding hills are covered with gre